**â€œOur platform runs on Kubernetes (AKS) hosted on Azure virtual machines and is designed as a multi-environment, region-based architecture. Each environmentâ€”such as US, India, SG, and AUSâ€”has its own public IP, Azure Load Balancer, and NGINX Ingress Controller installed via Helm.
Region-specific domains are mapped in DNS to the corresponding public IPs. Incoming traffic enters the cluster through the Ingress Controller, where TLS is terminated using Kubernetes secrets. The Ingress then performs host- and path-based routing to forward requests to internal ClusterIP services, which route traffic to the appropriate microservice podsâ€”such as EMS, TMS, CNS, AMS, WFH, VMS, and Space Managementâ€”running within environment-specific namespaces.
Only the Ingress layer is publicly exposed, while all application services remain internal, ensuring secure, scalable, and isolated deployments across environments.â€**


1ï¸âƒ£ RESUME BULLETS (ATS-FRIENDLY + ARCHITECT LEVEL)
ğŸ”¹ Core Architecture
Designed and operated a multi-region Kubernetes (AKS) platform on Azure VMs supporting environments such as US, India, SG, and AUS.
Implemented region-specific public IPs and Azure Load Balancers, each mapped via DNS to environment-specific domains.
Deployed NGINX Ingress Controllers using Helm per environment to handle secure external access.
ğŸ”¹ Traffic & Security
Configured TLS termination at the Ingress layer using Kubernetes TLS secrets.
Implemented host- and path-based routing to expose multiple microservices through a single domain per environment.
Ensured only Ingress is publicly accessible, while all backend services remain internal using ClusterIP services.
ğŸ”¹ Kubernetes & Microservices
Managed environment-level isolation using Kubernetes namespaces.
Deployed and maintained microservices including EMS, TMS, CNS, AMS, WFH, VMS, and Space Management.
Standardized ingress routing using environment-specific configuration files (e.g., azure-virtual.yaml).
ğŸ”¹ Operations & Tooling
Used Helm for ingress lifecycle management (installations and upgrades).
Managed container image access using Docker registry secrets.
Worked closely with CI/CD pipelines (Jenkins) for automated deployments into AKS namespaces.
2ï¸âƒ£ MANAGER / STAKEHOLDER EXPLANATION (NON-TECH FRIENDLY)
â€œWe built the platform in a way that each region like US, India, or Australia operates independently while still following the same architecture. Each region has its own public entry point and security layer, so issues in one region do not affect others.
Traffic is securely routed through a gateway component that handles encryption and intelligently forwards requests to the correct backend services. Internally, services are isolated and not exposed to the internet, which improves both security and scalability.
This design allows us to scale regions independently, onboard new regions quickly, and maintain strong security boundaries.â€
